---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Accessibility | Peptide Atlas" description="The Peptide Atlas accessibility approach and how to report a barrier." currentSection="" showDisclaimer={false}>
  <article>
    <p class="eyebrow">Inclusive access</p>
    <h1>Accessibility</h1>
    <p>Peptide Atlas aims to make its directory and editorial network usable with a wide range of devices, browsers, and assistive technologies.</p>
    <h2>Our approach</h2>
    <p>We design toward WCAG 2.2 Level AA practices, including semantic headings and landmarks, keyboard-accessible navigation, visible focus states, skip links, text alternatives for meaningful images, responsive layouts, and support for reduced-motion preferences.</p>
    <h2>Known limits</h2>
    <p>Some linked third-party documents, historical source files, or external sites may not meet the same accessibility goals. We do not claim formal conformance until an independent audit has verified it.</p>
    <h2>Report a barrier</h2>
    <p>If a page is difficult to use, send the URL, the task you were trying to complete, your browser or assistive technology if you are comfortable sharing it, and a description of the barrier through the <a href="/corrections/">corrections page</a>. We will use that information to investigate and prioritize a fix.</p>
  </article>
</Base>
